      <guid>https://zcheng-li.github.io/en/docs/my-blog/robotics/robo_l3/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;l3kinematics&#34;&gt;&#xA;  L3.Kinematics&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#l3kinematics&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Kinematcis describe the &lt;strong&gt;position&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;orientation&lt;/strong&gt; of a robot. These depends on the translational and rotational relationship of &lt;strong&gt;all the joints&lt;/strong&gt; for a robot. These are called &lt;strong&gt;transformation&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;kinematcis = position + orientation&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;transformation = translation + rotation&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Transformation is defined in terms of specific reference frames i.e. coordinate systems in space.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;transformation&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Transformation&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#transformation&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;pure-translation-transformation&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Pure Translation Transformation&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#pure-translation-transformation&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;post-img-view&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a data-fancybox=&#34;gallery&#34; href=&#34;https://zcheng-li.github.io/img/robo/L3_p11.png&#34;&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;          &lt;img src=&#34;https://zcheng-li.github.io/img/robo/L3_p11.png&#34; alt=&#34;Pure Translation Transformation&#34; /&gt;&#xA;          &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;          &lt;style&gt; &#xA;            .post-img-view{text-align:center} &#xA;          &lt;/style&gt; &#xA;      &lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
